Kafka lessons

in cmd - S:\kafka_2.13-2.5.0\kafka_2.13-2.5.0\bin\windows>

Step1: .\zookeeper-server-start.bat ..\..\config\zookeeper.properties
Step2: .\kafka-server-start.bat ..\..\config\server.properties

# Now server is running



Again open new cmd S:\kafka_2.13-2.5.0\kafka_2.13-2.5.0\bin\windows>

Step3: .\kafka-topics.bat --create --topic TEST --bootstrap-server localhost:9092
(to verify)  .\kafka-topics.bat --list --bootstrap-server localhost:9092
(to delete) .\kafka-topics.bat --delete --topic TEST --bootstrap-server localhost:9092

Step4:  .\kafka-console-producer.bat --broker-list localhost:9092 --topic test
and write messages


Again open new cmd S:\kafka_2.13-2.5.0\kafka_2.13-2.5.0\bin\windows>

Step5: .\kafka-console-consumer.bat --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --topic test --from-beginning
(we will  recieve messages here)